\par\plain {\f1\fs20\b0\i0 when characters of the so-called "Generation Q" fascinated audiences. Its namesake was the omnipotent entity from the TV series\~}{\f2\fs20\b0\i1 Star Trek \endash  The Next Generation}{\f1\fs20\b0\i0 , who exists beyond all ethical precepts and interpersonal rules. That was the place for the true sociopaths, whose question was no longer: "What is allowed?" but "What do I allow myself?". The negation of all maxims led to total freedom and absolute self-realisation. One\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s own needs and desires became the measure of all things. Arbitrariness and unpredictability had become the principle of life. People may still have known about good and evil, but they no longer cared.}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://christopher.marlowe.at/marlovian-hero/#fn22"}{\fldrslt\f1\fs20\b0\i0\super 2}}{\f1\fs20\b0\i0\ul\ulc0\super\cf4 2}{\f1\fs20\b0\i0 \~Of course, this philosophy was not entirely new. Its roots can be found in hedonism, surrealism and existentialism. Ultimately, all these tendencies cumulated in movies like\~}{\f2\fs20\b0\i1 The Silence of the Lambs}{\f1\fs20\b0\i0 ,\~}{\f2\fs20\b0\i1 Natural Born Killers}{\f1\fs20\b0\i0 ,\~}{\f2\fs20\b0\i1 From Dusk Till Dawn}{\f1\fs20\b0\i0 ,\~}{\f2\fs20\b0\i1 The Usual Suspects}{\f1\fs20\b0\i0 \~or\~}{\f2\fs20\b0\i1 Se7en}{\f1\fs20\b0\i0 . Serial killers, professional killers, psychopaths \endash  creatures who stand apart from society of their own free will \endash  became the new sympathisers and identification figures. Marlowe can claim to have established this trend as early as the 1590s.}{\f1\fs24\b0\i0  }
